{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a38bb0ac-b2dc-4e1c-bf74-6d7ce9ff7860","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** In xUnit, `Skip` is a property on `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`, not a separate attribute. All other frameworks use a standalone attribute alongside the test marker.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c8a8ea32-a1c4-4284-88ff-e255fef84c3e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tool calls needed.","outputTokens":326,"requestId":"0837:24D6F7:BE1355:DD3ABE:69EAC2A1"},"id":"b30eb23c-b6ca-4b99-8fd9-d51072321339","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:08:58.061Z","parentId":"15d20d0d-cabb-48f2-bba6-b7bf09a037f6"}
